        "created_at": "2025-10-03T19:46:04.551Z",
        "cooked": "<p>My rationale is that some presence is better than no presence.</p>\n<ol>\n<li>Could signal remove media transfers from the apk they distribute in the EU? No video and images means no CSAM distribution.</li>\n<li>Could signal mark the app as 18+ globally in the app stores and leave it up to google/apple? If there are no children on the platform then then there is nobody to groom.</li>\n<li>Since Signal already uses phone numbers could they query EU phone operators to see if the number is controlled by an adult?</li>\n<li>Could signal offer something else in addition to phone number based signups?</li>\n<li>Could Signal have an option to buy an account with crypto for a nominal fee like 10 USD? Children in EU do not have access to crypto and any accounts activated through those measures couldn‚Äôt not be children and could not affect anything else.</li>\n<li>Could signal split and create an entity that controls the backbone and an entity that develops the user facing app?</li>\n<li>Could signal leave the backbone open for other apps to use and have separate or even non related parties develop the user facing apps so that it doesn‚Äôt cross the monthly 45 million threshold?</li>\n<li>Could signal become data agnostic? Meaning they transfer data and it is up to the user applications how to interpret it.</li>\n<li>Could signal integrate optional Tor routing? I think Tor has been working on an easier to use implementation for years and years now, is it ready?</li>\n<li>Could signal take measures not to inflate active monthly user stats? Meaning use of the app is sending a message or receiving a message and actually reading it.</li>\n<li>Could signal argue that non discoverability of random people prevents the targeting of children because you can not find the children on the service? That would combine with measures of not allowing children on the service.</li>\n<li>Could signal argue that the no screenshots function serves as an anti cyber bullying measure? What children do is screenshot and share conversations to cause grief to each other. No media transfers would also eliminate a lot of the concerns about protecting the children from themselves and others.</li>\n<li>Could Signal implement an optional? p2p infrastructure that is then optionally? Tor routed? This could prevent data collection measures being forced upon Signal.</li>\n<li>Could signal create a web app?</li>\n<li>Could Signal collaborate with GrapheneOS?</li>\n</ol>",
